snippet.textDisplay:
On Amazon there are third party sellers who sell the product . These types of items are not fulfilled by Amazon it is directly shipped by a seller . And Some sellers will give compensation just for giving them a good review which is illegal .
The item becomes Amazon's choice on various factors like purchase , reviews , least returns .
So if in case the item was sold by a seller fulfilled by Amazon and he got good reviews . And that seller runs out of stock .
But there is another seller selling it .
The item will be shown as Amazon's choice .
The best options is always to go for items fulfilled by Amazon .
Seller orders are time consuming .
If there is any issue you first contact the seller then wait for response then file a claim .
Kinda hectic .
Prime items fulfilled by Amazon is the best option to go for .
Any issue Amazon will help and take care of it .
